channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Anthony Nesty’s role as U.S. Olympic men’s swimming head coach is a ‘vision’ fulfilled
item.description: Anthony Nesty was named head coach of Team USA Swimming and will lead the men's team at the Paris Olympics. He is the first Black head coach of the team.

item.title: Hundreds of millions at risk from Chinese shopping app malware
Star of Channel 4’s A Place In The Sun ‘in relationship with married man who has split from wife’
item.description: They are said to be spending a lot of time together.

item.title: Missing Jay Slater's dad breaks silence with heartbreaking question about search
item.description: Heartbroken Warren Slater, 58, spoke out after desperately spending two hours hiking through the ravine where Jay's phone last 'pinged' 16 days ago - the teenager has not been seen since June 17

item.title: Gathering of 70 centenarians breaks world record in Italy
item.description: An Italian retirement home chain's annual gathering of centenarians broke a Guinness World Record when 70 people who were at least 100 years old attended this year's event.

item.title: Ozempic may be linked to condition that causes blindness, but more research is needed
item.description: People taking Ozempic and Wegovy may be at increased risk of developing a debilitating eye condition that can cause irreversible vision loss, a study published in JAMA Ophthalmology finds.

item.title: Russian authorities detain suspect over St. Petersburg cafe blast
Emmerdale legend rushed to hospital after ‘chopping top of finger off’ on set
item.description: 'I was making a Bolognese, as you do.'

item.title: Gardeners urged to avoid common trick to deter slugs as it 'makes things worse'
item.description: Gardeners have long been told that a layer of crushed eggshells on the soil will put slugs off crossing it - because the shells are too spiky and uncomfortable for them to crawl over

item.title: Look: 11 pigs found wandering through California neighborhood
item.description: Authorities in California's San Diego County are trying to determine the origins of 11 pigs found wandering loose through a residential neighborhood.

item.title: Former NFL player charged with domestic battery after missing teenage son found 'safe and well'
item.description: Former NFL player Daniel Muir and his wife have been charged after allegedly hiding their teenage son from authorities following concerns that the boy was abused.

item.title: READ: Trump indictment related to hush money payment
Steamy TV series that has fans in a ‘chokehold’ just revealed best virginity losing scene
item.description: 'Just a wild, fantastic romp!'

item.title: MPs to have their summer holidays shortened if Labour win General Election
item.description: Keir Starmer said he wants to make progress on recruiting teachers, cutting the NHS backlog and getting police on the streets by the end of July - meaning recess could be crunched

item.title: Dog rescue volunteers help runaway horse in Arizona
item.description: Volunteers from a dog rescue in Arizona ended up helping out a four-legged animal quite a bit larger than their usual canines -- a runaway horse.

item.title: Britain’s election could be historic. Here’s what to know.
item.description: LONDON — Millions of Brits go to the polls Thursday, in an election likely to oust the Conservative Party that has dominated postwar politics and ruled the United Kingdom for the past 14 years.

item.title: Trump pleads not guilty to 34 felony counts
Biden ‘admits he may not be able to recover after debate disaster’
item.description: President Joe Biden has reportedly told an ally that he may not be able to salvage his campaign unless his next few performances are strong.

item.title: Drivers who get a flat battery could face £2,500 fine, expert warns
item.description: The Clean Neighbourhoods and Environment Act 2005 states that performing any work on a motor vehicle on the roadside, is described as "restricted works" and can see you fined

item.title: Stranger's license plate number earns lottery player a $50,000 prize
item.description: A Maryland man used a set of numbers he copied from another vehicle's license plate to play the lottery and scored a $50,000 prize.

item.title: Biden to meet with Democratic governors as he seeks to tamp down calls to step aside
item.description: President Joe Biden is set to meet with a group of Democratic governors on Wednesday as he and senior aides try to tamp down a growing sense of concern about his ability to remain the party's nominee in the November election.

item.title: The haunting Masters meltdown that changed Rory McIlroy's career
item.description: Slumped on his club, head buried in his arm, Rory McIlroy looked on the verge of tears.

item.title: German pundit slams key England star for doing ‘nothing’ at Euro 2024
item.description: 'He hasn't done anything in four games.'

item.title: 'I lost 5 stone in 6 months - how I did it and what I eat to keep it up'
item.description: The mum dropped five stone in six months without any surgery and didn't restrict her food - now, she feels 'more like herself than ever before'

item.title: Watch: Family searching for emu on the loose in South Carolina
item.description: Members of a South Carolina family are on the hunt for an escaped emu that has become a local celebrity on social media.
